Life is about to get even more expensive for South African motorists and consumers, as fuel prices go up yet again on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - The Energy Department announced petrol will increase by 54-cents a litre from Wednesday. READ: Petrol price to go up in May AA spokesperson, Layton Beard said increases over the past few months have tallied up to a significant amount, starting from a little over R14 per litre to approximately R16,67 in only six months. "From our point of view, this is absolutely ominous news and it really does come as a blow to many consumers," Beard said. South Africans will have to consider where they will absorb the costs of the increase.